                    "node": {
                        "created_at": "1765555205",
                        "id": "18027706736579840",
                        "text": "\ud83c\udf8b SAVE the details\ud83d\udc47\ud83c\udffc\n\n\u2728\u2728 Follow @upscaleadventurers for bucket list travel inspo! \u2728\u2728 \n\nAll the details \ud83d\udc47\nPlanning a trip to Japan and dreaming of wandering through Kyoto\u2019s iconic bamboo forests? \ud83c\udf3f Here\u2019s the difference between the famous one you\u2019ve seen all over IG\u2026 and the peaceful one just a short walk away.\n\n\u2728 The Reveal:\nThat quiet, empty bamboo path you saw in our reel? It wasn\u2019t Arashiyama\u2026 it was Adashino Bamboo Forest, only a 20-minute walk from the crowds.\n\nIf you want those serene, no-one-else-in-your-shot bamboo photos, head to Adashino right at opening (or a little before!).\n\n\ud83c\udf8b Arashiyama Bamboo Grove (Kyoto\u2019s most famous bamboo forest)\n\u2013 Hours: Open 24/7\n\u2013 Cost: Free\n\u2013 Best for: Iconic Kyoto experience, easy access, nearby shops + Tenryu-ji Temple\n\u2013 What to know: Always busy, especially from 8\u201311 am; trains drop visitors right into the district\n\u2013 Photo tip: Sunrise is your best chance for fewer crowds, but it\u2019s rarely empty\n\n\ud83c\udf8d Adashino Bamboo Forest (the peaceful alternative 20 min away)\n\u2013 Hours: 9:00\u201316:00 (varies slightly by season)\n\u2013 Cost: ~\u00a5500 per person\n\u2013 Best for: Quiet paths, no crowds, beautiful light through the bamboo\n\u2013 What to know: Located within Adashino Nenbutsu-ji Temple grounds, closes early, fewer tour groups\n\u2013 Photo tip: Arrive at or before opening for dreamy, empty-path photos \u2014 this is the secret to crowd-free bamboo shots\n\nIf Japan is on your bucket list, save this for your Kyoto itinerary \ud83d\uddfa\ufe0f\ud83c\uddef\ud83c\uddf5\n\n#KyotoJapan #KyotoItinerary #JapanTravelTips VisitJapan KyotoBambooForest Arashiyama AdashinoBambooForest AdventureCouples TravelCouples AsiaTravelGuide"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
