                            "profile_pic_url": "https://scontent-sjc6-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-19/445387881_445489758077083_2299083768654279838_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_s150x150_tt6&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InByb2ZpbGVfcGljLmRqYW5nby4xMDgwLmMyIn0&_nc_ht=scontent-sjc6-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=107&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2QF5Lp7NJcvbkUK49ndhMf2uqjLKkh00YBKYDnZ3lVhOgO3Y72ORRFR273KXiO3W-VA&_nc_ohc=yPgpP_D9MnAQ7kNvwExHLl1&_nc_gid=hXEaYwqxBjgG3p7aOFIuFg&edm=ANTKIIoBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AfvgWdT0HwpLzAgSs-TnJZyd5WzrzQkZ0z6Qdc6VEUE1dg&oe=69A02BA1&_nc_sid=d885a2",
                            "username": "breannastockholm"
                        },
                        "text": "For those womdering: it is not actually that empty but much better than the larger forest. It is also a much smaller section of bamboo. BUT the temple there is beautiful and there is a cafe right at the bottom of the entrance with great tea and coffee and a wonderful shop owner. And if you walk back into the main area of arashiyama, you will pass a lot of local shops with handmade goods. You will also see signs for cocoon art, definitely go up the steps into the shop. Some of the most unique souvenirs you could buy.",
